  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GFD and BSFP in Monguno 2016</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Borno State has been a scene of violent conflict for the last few years, which has caused unprecedented movement of populations. The conflict has left a significant number of people with limited access to food. The onset of the lean season has impacted the situation negatively, leading to a large increase of people in need of immediate food assistance. 
In response, AAH initiated an emergency response in Monguno to reduce under-nutrition and related mortality. The intervention strategy is an integrated response to comprehensively address, treat and further prevent malnutrition and includes the following sectors: Health, Nutrition, Water, Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH) and Food Security and Livelihoods (FSL).</narrative>
  </description>
